1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,794
<i>Let's see.</i>

2
00:00:02,877 --> 00:00:06,464
<i>Don't worry.</i>
<i>I'll make your life more bitter.</i>

3
00:00:06,548 --> 00:00:09,092
<i>I confronted my</i>
<i>wife because I found out…</i>

4
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:11,428
<i>that she had an affair.</i>

5
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:15,056
<i>With Lucas Santiago.</i>

6
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,184
[laughing]

7
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:21,062
- [Yuri grunting]
<i>- Edong!</i>

8
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,273
- [Egong grunts]
<i>- Yuri!</i>

9
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:28,528
<i>I told Erica that I'm willing</i>
<i>to tell Edong and everyone that</i>

10
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:30,822
<i>that we lied back</i>
<i>then to send him to jail.</i>

11
00:00:30,905 --> 00:00:31,823
<i>No!</i>

12
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,825
<i>The watch that was found</i>
<i>in the house wasn't Louisa's.</i>

13
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>- You were the first one to lie!</i>
<i>- We did lie.</i>

14
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:37,120
<i>Beth, it wasn't entirely our fault,</i>

15
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,788
<i>but we are also to blame.</i>

16
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:41,249
<i>Our only option is</i>
<i>to investigate the murder again.</i>

17
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:43,126
<i>You know my stand on that.</i>

18
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,669
<i>Our lives are at stake here,</i>

19
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,296
<i>and you still don't want to cooperate?</i>

20
00:00:49,257 --> 00:00:50,133
[phone chimes]

21
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:54,679
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental playing]

22
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:16,034
["Sabay Sabay Tayo" continues]

23
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:24,501
[Ryan] What's that?

24
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:30,173
[ominous music sting]

25
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:33,551
- Damn it!
- [phone shatters]

26
00:01:41,392 --> 00:01:48,316
[theme music playing]

27
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,304
You're not the only one
who made a mistake, Beth.

28
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:00,972
Mel and I did too.

29
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:05,602
The reason we let Erica
distance herself from us 14 years ago

30
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,020
was because we wanted to forget

31
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:09,188
how weak and vulnerable we were then.

32
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:11,816
But we're not kids anymore.

33
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:15,528
And we're not weak and vulnerable anymore.

34
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:17,739
We have to let all of this go.

35
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:22,118
We need to unite and correct our mistake.

36
00:03:22,201 --> 00:03:24,662
Then do it by yourselves!

37
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,372
Leave me out of it!

38
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:29,083
We have freedom of choice, right?

39
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,168
[exasperated sigh]

40
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:34,881
Don't tell me you're
taking things personally?

41
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:39,010
Is this why you're being
too aggressive towards Erica?

42
00:03:39,802 --> 00:03:43,640
Why are you so mad at
her even though she's helping us?

43
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:50,813
You know, I noticed you never
respected her when we were kids.

44
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:54,776
You always looked down on her.

45
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,819
Like she's beneath you.

46
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,698
But it's different now, Beth.

47
00:04:01,407 --> 00:04:03,034
What? You still can't accept

48
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:05,453
that you need
to respect and listen to her now?

49
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:09,749
Just tell it to me straight.

50
00:04:09,832 --> 00:04:11,459
What do you want to say, huh?

51
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:12,961
That I'm jealous of her?

52
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:16,172
Because she's a lawyer
and everyone respects her?

53
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:19,968
While I'm just a teacher now
and my life turned out this way?!

54
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:21,928
That's not what I'm saying!

55
00:04:22,011 --> 00:04:23,763
You don't have to say it!

56
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:26,099
I know that's what you all think!

57
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:27,976
That I was so full of myself back then,

58
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:30,270
thinking that I'd succeed,

59
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:32,689
become a popular journalist,

60
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:34,399
and be able to travel the world.

61
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:36,734
But in the end,
I turned out like my mother!

62
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,738
The world was so big
when I was dreaming then.

63
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:44,867
But I just ended up living in
a small house here in Amurao.

64
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,577
That's as far as I got!

65
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:47,829
Congratulations to me!

66
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:48,830
[loud bang]

67
00:04:48,913 --> 00:04:53,793
[sullen music playing]

68
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:15,523
[sullen music continues]

69
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:28,870
Love. Love.

70
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,001
I thought you were happy with our life.

71
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,921
Because I'm happy, Beth.

72
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:42,717
I know we have a lot of problems.

73
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:44,677
But I'm happy.

74
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:45,845
[music fades]

75
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,473
I'm content, Beth.

76
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,100
Because I have Chloe.

77
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,604
- I have you.
- [Beth sobs]

78
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,816
Love, what we talked about back there…

79
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,235
It's not about us.

80
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:03,905
Alice has been acting like a therapist

81
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:05,823
ever since she started going to therapy.

82
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:09,494
Edong was the one we were talking about.

83
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:12,663
They want me
to admit I lied about the watch.

84
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:15,708
Love, you know, right?

85
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:19,587
You know why I lied
about that watch, right?

86
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:23,466
That was the only way
I knew to put Edong in jail.

87
00:06:24,425 --> 00:06:28,221
Until now, I believe
I did the right thing back then.

88
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:32,266
But if I admit that I was wrong,

89
00:06:33,684 --> 00:06:36,562
I'm afraid that once Chloe finds out,

90
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:39,315
she won't understand why I did that.

91
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:43,319
[sullen music resumes]

92
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:49,033
Love…

93
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:50,993
Love…

94
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:54,455
Love, I won't be able to bear it

95
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,708
if Chloe starts seeing me differently.

96
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,461
Her respect for me…

97
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,713
the way she looks up to me…

98
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:05,424
it's very important to me.

99
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:08,678
Its, it's all I have.

100
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:10,012
[sobs]

101
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,431
There you go again.

102
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:13,099
"It's all you have"?

103
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,770
You keep talking like you have nothing.

104
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,730
Like our life is worthless!

105
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:23,401
Love, that's not what I meant.

106
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:25,403
That's not it.

107
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,822
You know, Beth,

108
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:31,409
Alice never looked down on you.

109
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:33,786
You know who did that?

110
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:36,581
Yourself.

111
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:41,127
[sullen music continues]

112
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,379
So you're also a therapist now?

113
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,632
Then you can all pretend
to be therapists for all I care!

114
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:55,516
Come on, tell me.

115
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:01,772
If you were given a chance to start over,

116
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:06,944
would you still
choose this life we have now?

117
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:09,989
[music becomes somber]

118
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,241
Would you still choose me?

119
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,125
Yeah.

120
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:23,419
Of course!

121
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:27,006
[somber music continues]

122
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,553
[sniffles, sighs deeply]

123
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,898
[sniffles, sobs]

124
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:47,693
[somber music continues]

125
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:50,905
[Alice] That's what
she thought this whole time?

126
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:54,158
That we were judging her life?

127
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:58,412
We always tell
her that she has the best family.

128
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:00,456
We were genuinely happy for her

129
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,542
because we thought
she was happy for herself.

130
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:09,006
- [music fades]
- Oh, God, the look on Ryan's face I…

131
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,134
I feel so guilty.

132
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,053
Hey, hey.

133
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:18,266
Look, it's not your fault. Okay?

134
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:21,018
Whatever Beth's issue is,

135
00:09:21,102 --> 00:09:24,021
isn't it better for
them to deal with it now

136
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:26,315
rather than having
it explode on them later?

137
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:33,614
[phone buzzing]

138
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,785
I have to take this. Sorry.

139
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,083
I told you I can't go back yet.

140
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:50,590
Can you just deal with it yourself?

141
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:51,924
I need more time.

142
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:53,551
[man] <i>Scott, this is your deal.</i>

143
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,178
<i>The Johnsons trust you, and want you here.</i>

144
00:09:56,846 --> 00:09:58,472
<i>If you don't come</i>
<i>back and see this through,</i>

145
00:09:58,556 --> 00:09:59,932
<i>the deal might not go through.</i>

146
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:01,934
<i>We can't let that happen.</i>

147
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,020
<i>We need this.</i>

148
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,316
Alright.

149
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,819
I'll call them,
and I'll see what I can do.

150
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,279
Okay?

151
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:20,828
They want you back?

152
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:25,374
[sighs]

153
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:29,462
[gentle music playing]

154
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:31,047
What if you just go home

155
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,174
and you can continue
your therapy in the US?

156
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:35,384
Scott, no. I can't.

157
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,178
I don't want to.

158
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:41,182
You know, I've come so far with Doc Isla,

159
00:10:41,265 --> 00:10:43,142
and if I switch therapist now,

160
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:46,228
I'm afraid I won't get the answers I need.

161
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:48,939
I'm so close, Scott.

162
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:50,316
I know I am.

163
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,612
If you really have to go…

164
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:56,822
And leave you here, alone?

165
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,116
No way.

166
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,536
I'm sorry. I'm…

167
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:04,914
- I'm already causing so much trouble--
- Shh. Shh.

168
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:09,502
[gentle music continues]

169
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:17,218
No. You're not.

170
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:19,178
- [Alice sighs heavily]
- And stop thinking that.

171
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:21,430
If you need me to be here,

172
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:23,682
then I'll be here, too.

173
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:28,187
[gentle music continues]

174
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:39,740
[music fades]

175
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:42,785
[sighs, sniffles]

176
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:46,747
[sighs]

177
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:56,215
[sobs]

178
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,638
[Margie] What happened?

179
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:04,473
- Hmm?
- [sighs]

180
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:09,520
Is this worth it, Mom?

181
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:14,984
What if it's not?

182
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:19,738
What if after everything,

183
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:22,491
what I've been dreading still happens?

184
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:26,579
What if I lose everything?

185
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:32,293
[somber music playing]

186
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:33,961
Even if that happens,

187
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:36,964
just pick yourself up again.

188
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:39,925
Start over.

189
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,263
You've done that before.

190
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:47,600
You rebelled against your dad.

191
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:51,270
You dropped out of med school.

192
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:55,149
And you had to start all over again

193
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:58,444
as a stylist without your father's help.

194
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:00,654
But I had you.

195
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:03,282
You helped me.

196
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:05,993
It was nothing.

197
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:07,286
This…

198
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:09,705
This is all you.

199
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:15,169
I can just imagine
how hard it must have been.

200
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:20,132
You were alone and
you didn't have a support system,

201
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,884
but you did it.

202
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:24,845
You became successful on your own.

203
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:26,764
So I…

204
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:30,893
I believe and I'm
sure you can do it again.

205
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:33,312
You can do it again.

206
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,274
It was really tough, Mom.

207
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:42,112
Dad cut me off financially and,

208
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,240
I was really struggling.

209
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,035
And if you didn't help me,

210
00:13:48,118 --> 00:13:49,411
I would have failed.

211
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:56,085
You gave me
that money so I could start again.

212
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:59,630
You helped me even though you knew

213
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:02,258
Dad would be angry if he found out.

214
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,845
I shouldn't have kept my support a secret.

215
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:09,223
Like it's something to be ashamed of.

216
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:11,183
You're my daughter.

217
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,727
It's my responsibility to support you.

218
00:14:13,811 --> 00:14:16,063
I shouldn't have been scared of your dad.

219
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:19,733
[somber music continues]

220
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:22,111
I know I haven't been a good mom.

221
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:24,363
I have a lot of shortcomings.

222
00:14:26,156 --> 00:14:27,741
But I'm here now.

223
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:31,036
If you need anything, I will support you.

224
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:34,582
If you want to get away from everything,

225
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:38,252
if you want to go back to Amurao,

226
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:41,046
that's fine. I will go with you.

227
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:43,716
Okay?

228
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,218
- Come here.
- Thanks, Mom.

229
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:51,015
[sobs]

230
00:14:56,145 --> 00:15:01,483
[music becomes unsettling]

231
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:23,380
[unsettling music continues]

232
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:51,617
- [laughter]
- [young Lucas] Come on!

233
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,119
[Dolores] <i>Let's eat. Oh!</i>

234
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:55,955
- [young Lucas] Come on, fight back!
[laughs]

235
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:58,666
- [slaps]
- [Dolores wailing]

236
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:00,459
<i>You think I'm proud of you, Dolores?</i>

237
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:04,213
<i>Be grateful I still come home to you.</i>

238
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:08,467
- [Edong grunts]
- [Dolores screams, cries]

239
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:10,552
[Dolores groans]

240
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:11,762
[Edong] <i>Argh!</i>

241
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:15,808
- [unsettling music continues]
- [birds twitter]

242
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:30,322
- [music fades]
- [crying softly]

243
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:38,789
[laughing softly]

244
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:47,715
[crying, laughing]

245
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:55,305
[wheezes, cries]

246
00:16:56,432 --> 00:16:57,599
[sniffles]

247
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:01,270
[crying, laughing]

248
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,271
[slaps]

249
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:05,816
[laughing]

250
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:10,362
[slaps, smacks]

251
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:12,990
- [slaps, smacks]
- [breathing heavily]

252
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:14,366
[smacks]

253
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,451
[exhales]

254
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:20,164
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental playing]

255
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:47,733
[music turns unsettling]

256
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:11,215
[keypad clacking]

257
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:20,474
[phone chimes]

258
00:18:20,557 --> 00:18:25,896
[unsettling music continues]

259
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:57,386
[unsettling music continues]

260
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:11,608
[phone chimes]

261
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:27,833
[unsettling music continues]

262
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:50,522
"I'M NOT DONE MAKING YOU PAY.

263
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:52,107
MEL ALREADY LOST WHAT SHE VALUES.

264
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,317
YOU TOOK MY BROTHER FROM ME.

265
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,902
I'LL TAKE MORE FROM YOU."

266
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:59,323
[unsettling music continues]

267
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:14,504
<i>Love, did you take our picture from here?</i>

268
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:16,089
<i>No, maybe Chloe did.</i>

269
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:18,926
[sniffles]

270
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,056
- [panicked breaths]
- [music fades]

271
00:20:24,681 --> 00:20:25,974
[phone chimes]

272
00:20:28,185 --> 00:20:29,144
[Ryan] What is it?

273
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:33,065
[ominous music sting]

274
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:40,030
[ominous music continues]

275
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:41,114
Give it to me.

276
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:47,621
"YOU TOOK MY BROTHER FROM ME.
I'LL TAKE MORE FROM YOU."

277
00:20:47,704 --> 00:20:48,705
What is this?

278
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:50,415
Who's it from?

279
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,459
Is it from Edong?

280
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:54,253
Why does he have this?

281
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:58,465
Remember, I noticed it was missing before?

282
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:01,551
Don't you remember me asking you about it?

283
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:04,179
We thought Chloe just used it for school.

284
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,597
He got in here?!

285
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,058
[Ryan huffs]

286
00:21:09,184 --> 00:21:10,936
- Damn it!
- [phone shatters]

287
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:16,108
[ominous music continues]

288
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:21,655
[whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

289
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:48,098
[laughing]

290
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:52,644
[whistling continues]

291
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:56,023
<i>- We're going.</i>
- [Tim]<i> Where?</i>

292
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,899
<i>To take back what's mine.</i>

293
00:21:57,983 --> 00:22:01,111
<i>We want to find out</i>
<i>who really killed Louisa.</i>

294
00:22:01,194 --> 00:22:03,280
<i>I know where you can start. I'll help.</i>

295
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,073
<i>Didn't you hear what I said to Alice?</i>

296
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:07,576
<i>I heard everything, Beth!</i>
<i>Even the things I shouldn't have heard!</i>

297
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:09,661
<i>I don't know what you want me to say!</i>

298
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:11,413
<i>I don't know what</i>
<i>I want to hear from you!</i>

299
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,956
<i>If you don't want to help, I will.</i>

300
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:16,084
<i>You're looking for people</i>
<i>who could have a motive to hurt Louisa?</i>

301
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:18,837
<i>Do you remember Kyle,</i>
<i>your former schoolmate?</i>

302
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,797
<i>He had a fight with Louisa right before.</i>
